The paper discusses the modeling of neural activities in the brain using the Izhikevich model, which is a common approach in the field of computational neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of genetic algorithms for optimizing the model parameters, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The study aims to improve the accuracy of the model, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the potential applications of the improved model in large-scale neural network simulations, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.CE (Computational Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
